Tuples are lists of a fixed size.
It is implemented as a subtype.

states.pp:
α : Type u,
n : ℕ,
cons_head_tail : ∀ (v : vector α n.succ), cons v.head v.tail = v,
h : list.nil.length = n.succ
⊢ cons (head ⟨list.nil α, h⟩) (tail ⟨list.nil α, h⟩) = ⟨list.nil α, h⟩

α : Type u,
n : ℕ,
a : α,
v : vector α n
⊢ (cons a v).to_list = a :: v.to_list

α : Type u,
n : ℕ,
a : α,
v_val : list α,
v_property : v_val.length = n
⊢ (cons a ⟨v_val, v_property⟩).to_list = a :: to_list ⟨v_val, v_property⟩

α : Type u,
n m : ℕ,
v : vector α n,
w : vector α m
⊢ (v.append w).to_list = v.to_list ++ w.to_list

α : Type u,
n m : ℕ,
w : vector α m,
v_val : list α,
v_property : v_val.length = n
⊢ (append ⟨v_val, v_property⟩ w).to_list = to_list ⟨v_val, v_property⟩ ++ w.to_list

α : Type u,
n m : ℕ,
v_val : list α,
v_property : v_val.length = n,
w_val : list α,
w_property : w_val.length = m
⊢ (append ⟨v_val, v_property⟩ ⟨w_val, w_property⟩).to_list =
    to_list ⟨v_val, v_property⟩ ++ to_list ⟨w_val, w_property⟩

α : Type u,
n m : ℕ,
v : vector α m
⊢ (drop n v).to_list = list.drop n v.to_list

α : Type u,
n m : ℕ,
v_val : list α,
v_property : v_val.length = m
⊢ (drop n ⟨v_val, v_property⟩).to_list = list.drop n (to_list ⟨v_val, v_property⟩)

α : Type u,
n m : ℕ,
v : vector α m
⊢ (take n v).to_list = list.take n v.to_list

α : Type u,
n m : ℕ,
v_val : list α,
v_property : v_val.length = m
⊢ (take n ⟨v_val, v_property⟩).to_list = list.take n (to_list ⟨v_val, v_property⟩)
